      <body>
         
 <!-- There is no in-the-comic header including the title and date on this page, so I have eliminated the header element. -->
         
         <div type="panelGrp" xml:id="Transformers2012-01-11"><!-- Make sure that the value of this xml:id matches the idno from line 35 above. If there is a setting, weather, activities, or Bechdel test, tag them in the <div> with ana="" -->
            
            <cbml:panel n="1" characters="#UltraMagnus #RodimusPrime #Drift" ana="Cybertron"><!-- In each of the four panel blocks, record the characters that appear in the panel.   -->
               <note resp="#r-LV" type="panelDesc">Rodimus Prime stands on a raised platform giving a speech. Ultra Magnus stands behind him to the viewer's left. Drift stands opposite Ultra Magnus with his hands on the hilt of his sword. Several unnamed and unidentifiable Cybertronians are visible standing in a crowd below the platform.</note><!-- Put your r-name from the taxonomy (e.g., #r-HJ, #r-DM, #r-AL, #r-KS) as the value of the resp attribute. Give a quick description of what happens in this panel -->
               <cbml:caption>Cybertron. Yesterday.</cbml:caption>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">They say that 12 million years ago, on this very spot, the first <emph>Cybertronian</emph> realized he could <emph>change shape.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">Six million years ago, right here, <emph>Nova Prime</emph> told the world that he'd built an <emph>ark.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">And four million years ago <emph>to the day,</emph> Optimus Prime stood where I now stand and turned down Megatron's first and only invitation to <emph>surrender.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">What happens here <emph>tomorrow</emph> will rank alongside those moments. Tomorrow, this patch of land becomes a <emph>launch pad.</emph> Tomorrow, I will board the <emph>Lost Light</emph> and set off in search of our ancestors.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">They were known as the <emph>Knights of Cybertron.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">They're <emph>real.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">I'm going to <emph>find them.</emph></cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">And I want all of <emph>you</emph>to come with me.</cbml:balloon><!-- Put in the character who is speaking. If there are no speech bubbles, remove this line. If it's a different type of bubble than a speech bubble, change the @type value.-->
               <!-- Add a second (or third!) <cbml:balloon> if there are multiple speech bubbles in a panel -->
               <!-- In addition to <cbml:balloon>, you also have the choice of <cbml:caption> for text that is not in a speech balloon (this will probably be incredibly rare in our corpus), <sound>, <figure> for music, or <floatingText type="diegetic">. -->
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="2" characters="#RodimusPrime" ana="#Cybertron"><!-- In panels 2, 3, and 4, also record the transition type according to McCloud using the tr- value from the taxonomy -->
               <note resp="#r-LV" type="panelDesc">Four unnamed Cybertronians watch a broadcast of Rodimus Prime's speech.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime"><emph>Bumblebee</emph> says it's your duty to stay here, on a planet you no longer recognize, among people who resent you for the sacrifices you've made in their name.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">I say: you've <emph>done</emph> your duty. The war is <emph>over.</emph> That day you never thought would come? That's <emph>today.</emph></cbml:balloon>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="3" characters="#RodimusPrime #Wheeljack #Prowl" ana="#Cybertron">
               <note resp="#r-LV" type="panelDesc">Wheeljack glances over his shoulder at the crowd. Prowl stares to the viewer's left, crossing his arms and scowling.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#RodimusPrime">You've earned the right to see the universe without a gun in your hand.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Wheeljack">Kid knows how to work a crowd. We could be witnessing a <emph>mass exodus</emph> at this rate.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Prowl">Pffft.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Wheeljack">Are you <emph>disagreeing,</emph> or are your pistons playing up?</cbml:balloon>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="4" characters="#Prowl" ana="#Cybertron">
               <note resp="#r-LV" type="panelDesc">A close-up of Prowl talking.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Prowl">Wheeljack, I can observe 800 moving objects and compute their direction of travel in 0.5 seconds. This is no different.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Prowl">As soon as Rodimus said he was leaving I mentally compiled two lists: those who'd go with him, and those who'd stay behind.</cbml:balloon>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#Prowl">Trust me, all reliable indicators suggest that tomorrow's launch...</cbml:balloon>
            </cbml:panel>
            
